# Auto-push to GitHub

After making code changes in this project:

1. Commit with a clear message when the work is complete (user does not need to ask).
2. Push to GitHub immediately using saved SSH auth — do not ask the user to push.
3. Remote: `git@github.com:ayanlea24-ui/Third-brain-.git` on branch `main`.
4. If HTTPS remote fails, use `git remote set-url origin git@github.com:ayanlea24-ui/Third-brain-.git` then push.
5. Never commit `.env` or secrets (respect `.gitignore`).

Local dev uses `npm run dev`; production on Render uses `npm start`.
